<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-8a-4">
  <p>
    Let 
    <me>
      T(x) = 3 - x + \frac{1}{3}x^2 - \frac{1}{9}x^3 + \cdots + 3 \cdot \left(- \frac{1}{3} \right)^n x^n + \cdots
    </me>.
  </p>

  <p>
    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Explain why <m>T(x)</m> is a geometric series and identify the values of <m>a</m> and <m>r</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Use <xref ref="eq-8a-3-infinite-geometric-sum">Equation</xref> to find a single fraction that represents the value of <m>T(x)</m>.  For which values of <m>x</m> is this equation valid?
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Consider the function <m>f(x) = 9 (3 + x)^{-1}</m>.  Determine <m>f(0)</m>, <m>f'(0)</m>, <m>f''(0)</m>, and <m>f'''(0)</m>.  What is the degree <m>3</m> Taylor polynomial centered at <m>0</m> for the function <m>f(x)</m>?
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          How is your work in (c) connected to the original given series <m>T(x)</m>?
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>
</exploration>

